Class trussoptimizater.Elements.Element extends java.util.Observable implements Serializable

Serialized Fields

number

int number
Element number, should be between 0 and the elementArray.size. Each element has to be assigned a number as it is used in the analysis part of the program. Elements numbers have to be updated when elements are removed in the element arrays.

Perhaps a better way to do this would be to scap this attrivute and just use the element index in the array as this is updated automatically.

highLighted

boolean highLighted
Boolean representing whether the element is currently highlighted

Probably should be moved to GUI side, but currently convienant to have it here

selected

boolean selected
Boolean representing whether the element is currently selected

Probably should be moved to GUI side, but currently convienant to have it here

char type

node

Node node
The node that the joint is pa

connectingBars

java.util.ArrayList<E> connectingBars
ArrayList of all bars making up the joint

chord1

Bar chord1

chord2

Bar chord2

brace1

Bar brace1

brace2

Bar brace2

geometry

double geometry

geometryCheck

java.lang.String geometryCheck
Joint have to pass specfic geometry tests. When they have been checked they should be set to either:

  • Joint.FAIL
  • Joint.PASS

plastificationCheck

java.lang.String plastificationCheck
Joint have to be checked that the chord faces will not buckle.

When they have been checked they should be set to either:

  • Joint.FAIL
  • Joint.PASS

punchingShearCheck

java.lang.String punchingShearCheck
Joint have to be checked against punching shear. ie if the braces have large axial force and are small in diameter and the chords have a large diamter the joint will most probably fail.

When they have been checked they should be set to either:

  • Joint.FAIL
  • Joint.PASS
